According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Electrical Discharge Machining (EDM) Market was valued at USD 2.24 billion in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 2.40 billion in 2025 to USD 3.56 billion by 2032, registering a CAGR of 7.0% during the forecast period. Market growth is being fueled by increasing demand for high-precision components across aerospace, automotive, electronics, and medical device industries. Technological advancements, including AI-driven automation, IoT integration, and improved spark erosion techniques, are further enhancing machining accuracy, productivity, and operational efficiency, accelerating adoption worldwide.
